{"ts": "2026-06-07T22:29:02.774660+00:00", "update": {"tools": {"messages": [{"type": "tool", "data": {"content": [{"type": "text", "text": "successfully downloaded text file (SHA: 050442fab01646f6bfe0285ef981bdba071e0d4b)", "id": "lc_7d8a1b97-d45a-4849-87c1-78ae6f492f6b"}, {"type": "text", "text": "import request from '@/utils/request'\n\nexport function login(data) {\n  return request({\n    url: '/vue-admin-template/user/login',\n    method: 'post',\n    data,\n  })\n}\n\nexport function getInfo(token) {\n  return request({\n    url: '/vue-admin-template/user/info',\n    method: 'get',\n    params: { token },\n  })\n}\n\nexport function logout() {\n  return request({\n    url: '/vue-admin-template/user/logout',\n    method: 'post',\n  })\n}\n", "id": "lc_582c87c7-3670-4f54-ae45-8593f4ef5f06"}], "additional_kwargs": {}, "response_metadata": {}, "type": "tool", "name": "get_file_contents", "id": "e6fe583c-948d-4afc-bbdb-4864b77faa9f", "tool_call_id": "call_4a56da7752504389b312647f", "artifact": null, "status": "success"}}]}}}
{"ts": "2026-06-07T22:29:17.005066+00:00", "update": {"model": {"messages": [{"type": "ai", "data": {"content": "### Login & Permission Flow in `T01_R02`\n\nThe app uses **Vue Router navigation guards** (`router.beforeEach`) to enforce authentication and authorization. The core logic lives in **`src/permission.js`**.\n\n---\n\n#### **1. Navigation Guard Entry Point**\nEvery route change triggers `router.beforeEach`. The guard:\n1. Starts a progress bar (`NProgress`).\n2. Sets the page title.\n3. Checks for a **token** via `getToken()` (reads `Admin-Token` from local storage using the `store` library).\n\n---\n\n#### **2. Token-Based Decision Tree**\n\n```\nHas Token?\n├── YES\n│   ├── Navigating to /login? → Redirect to '/' (already logged in)\n│   └── Otherwise\n│       ├── User info already in Vuex? (store.getters.name)\n│       │   └── YES → Allow navigation (next())\n│       └── NO → Fetch user info\n│           ├── Success → Allow navigation (next())\n│           └── Failure → Token invalid/expired\n│               ├── Remove token (resetToken)\n│               ├── Show error message\n│               └── Redirect to /login?redirect={original_path}\n│\n└── NO\n    ├── Route in whitelist? (['/login'])\n    │   └── YES → Allow navigation (next())\n    └── NO → Redirect to /login?redirect={original_path}\n```\n\n---\n\n#### **3. When User Info Is Fetched**\n- **Only when a token exists but `store.getters.name` is empty.**\n- This happens:\n  - On first load after a page refresh (Vuex state is reset but token persists in storage).\n  - After a successful login (token is set, but `getInfo` hasn't been called yet).\n- The fetch calls `GET /vue-admin-template/user/info?token=...`.\n\n---\n\n#### **4. Token Validation Failure Handling**\nIf `getInfo` fails (e.g., token expired, server rejects it):\n1. **`store.dispatch('user/resetToken')`** is called:\n   - Removes `Admin-Token` from local storage.\n   - Resets Vuex state (`name`, `avatar` → empty strings).\n2. **Error message** is shown via `ElMessage.error`.\n3. **Redirect** to `/login?redirect=${to.path}` — the original destination is preserved so the user can return after re-login.\n\n---\n\n#### **5. Login & Logout**\n\n| Action | API Call | Side Effects |\n|--------|----------|--------------|\n| **Login** | `POST /vue-admin-template/user/login` | Stores token in Vuex + local storage |\n| **Logout** | `POST /vue-admin-template/user/logout` | Removes token, resets router, clears Vuex state |\n\n---\n\n#### **Key Files**\n| File | Role |\n|------|------|\n| `src/permission.js` | Navigation guard — the \"gatekeeper\" |\n| `src/store/modules/user.js` | Vuex module handling login/logout/getInfo/resetToken |\n| `src/utils/auth.js` | Token get/set/remove from local storage |\n| `src/api/user.js` | API calls for login, getInfo, logout |\n\n---\n\n#### **Summary**\nThe app uses a **token-first** approach: if a token exists, it trusts it until `getInfo` proves otherwise. User info is fetched **lazily** (only when needed and not yet in Vuex). If token validation fails at any point, the app **clears the token**, shows an error, and **redirects to login** with a `redirect` query parameter to preserve the user's intended destination.", "additional_kwargs": {"refusal": null}, "response_metadata": {"token_usage": {"completion_tokens": 1256, "prompt_tokens": 9283, "total_tokens": 10539, "completion_tokens_details": {"accepted_prediction_tokens": null, "audio_tokens": 0, "reasoning_tokens": 494, "rejected_prediction_tokens": null, "image_tokens": 0}, "prompt_tokens_details": {"audio_tokens": 0, "cached_tokens": 9024, "cache_write_tokens": 0, "video_tokens": 0}, "cost": 0, "is_byok": true, "cost_details": {"upstream_inference_cost": 0.0004132072, "upstream_inference_prompt_cost": 6.15272e-05, "upstream_inference_completions_cost": 0.00035168}}, "model_provider": "openai", "model_name": "xiaomi/mimo-v2.5-20260422", "system_fingerprint": null, "id": "gen-1780871342-yWHqLOselQHV1yvxlvx7", "finish_